The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Deadline set for Maytas
                                                                                                               Deadline set for Maytas
          G.S. RADHAKRISHNA                              
	Hyderabad, June 23: Andhra Pradesh chief minister Y.S. Rajasekhar Reddy has given an ultimatum to beleaguered Maytas Infra to submit the financial closure plan of the Hyderabad metro rail project by June 30 along with a performance security deposit of Rs 240 crore.        
	At a meeting yesterday with Maytas chairman K. Ramalingam  the government nominee to the board  Reddy said that the project must be grounded in the next four months and completed before 2014.         
	Ramalingam was seeking a six months extension on the financial closure..        
	If Maytas fails to meet the requirements by the end of this month, the metro deal with the state government stands cancelled.         
	The rebidding for the project is likely in the third week of August.        
	Maytas is promoted by the kin of B. Ramalinga Raju, the jailed promoter of Satyam Computer.                                                                                                                                       
